SEC. 4.

The Center shall be a collaboration between the City Government of Dagupan and the National Commission for Culture and the Arts (NCCA), herein referred to as the "Commission," with its concerned affiliated cultural agencies and pertinent academic and private sector partners, and members of the community, wit its site, structures, governance, organization, operations, and development to be provided for by mutual agreement between the parties, to be executed and published within one (1) year from the effectivity of this Act.

Within thirty (30) Calendar days upon effectivity of this Implementing Rules and Regulations (IRR), a Technical Working Group (TWG) shall be created, composed of representatives from the City Government of Dagupan and the NCCA, which shall be responsible for the following:

a. Act as the lead body in coordinating and collating inputs from the different stakeholders for the establishment of the Center;

b. Draft the necessary Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) and/or its amendment regarding the Center's site, structures, governance, organization, operations, and development;

c. Ensure the execution and publication of the MOA; and
